[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":694},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages\u002F":671,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages\u002F":680},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20200923\u002F2032860736\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":655,"date":656,"description":19,"extension":302,"lang":657,"meta":658,"navigation":659,"path":660,"readingMinutes":661,"seo":662,"standalone":663,"stem":664,"tags":665,"tldr":668,"updated":656,"url":669,"__hash__":670},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-10-adding-pages.md","(10) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Adding New Pages","6370682302",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":650},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,49,56,59,68,79,86,92,97,103,107,110,120,286,289,295,298,325,328,557,560,566,569,580,640,643,646],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This post walks through how to add new pages to Hexo.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"adding-pages","Adding pages",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"First, why add pages at all. Let's open the Hexo project we built earlier. To save you ",[28,29,30],"del",{},"goldfish-brain"," moments forgetting the command, fire up the dev server in your terminal:",[33,34,39],"pre",{"className":35,"code":36,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","hexo s\n","cmd","",[40,41,42],"code",{"__ignoreMap":38},[43,44,47],"span",{"class":45,"line":46},"line",1,[43,48,36],{},[17,50,51,52,55],{},"Once the dev server is running, you'll notice most blogs have a page about the author — an \"about\" page. If you check your site, there's no such page. Trying ",[40,53,54],{},"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost:4000\u002Fabout\u002F"," won't work either.",[17,57,58],{},"Stop the dev server, then run this in the terminal:",[33,60,62],{"className":35,"code":61,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"hexo new page about\n",[40,63,64],{"__ignoreMap":38},[43,65,66],{"class":45,"line":46},[43,67,61],{},[17,69,70,71,74,75,78],{},"Hexo will create ",[40,72,73],{},"about\u002Findex.md"," under ",[40,76,77],{},"source",". That's your future about page.",[17,80,81],{},[82,83],"img",{"alt":84,"src":85},"about","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-03%2013.34.57.png",[17,87,88,89,91],{},"Restart the dev server. Now if you hit ",[40,90,54],{},", the page shows up.",[17,93,94],{},[82,95],{"alt":84,"src":96},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-03%2013.37.38.png",[17,98,99,100,102],{},"It's blank, and that's normal — you haven't put any content in ",[40,101,73],{}," yet. What goes there is up to you.",[12,104,106],{"id":105},"stripping-the-template","Stripping the template",[17,108,109],{},"You might want your new page to use your own custom HTML instead of the theme's template. Hexo can do that. I'll demo this with the about page we just created.",[17,111,112,113,115,116,119],{},"First, rename ",[40,114,73],{}," to ",[40,117,118],{},"index.html",", clear all the content, and put in:",[33,121,125],{"className":122,"code":123,"language":124,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003C!DOCTYPE html>\n\u003Chtml lang=\"zh-Hant-TW\">\n\u003Chead>\n  \u003Cmeta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  \u003Cmeta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  \u003Ctitle>About Me\u003C\u002Ftitle>\n\u003C\u002Fhead>\n\u003Cbody>\n  \u003Ch1>This is a heading\u003C\u002Fh1>\n\u